detailedDescription.articleBody: Dee Dee Davis is an American actress and comedian, best known for her role as Bryana Thomkins on The Bernie Mac Show, for which she won a Young Artist Award in 2004. She guest-starred in Strong Medicine, House, and The Game. Davis took a break from acting in 2007 to focus on school. In February 2017, Davis announced that she is pregnant with her first child.
